<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Yellow-brown, or in fresh specimens, more golden tan, with distinctly brown antemedial and postmedial lines, and veins accented by the same brown coloration, all of which strongly contrast against the lighter ground color.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="apomorphies">
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Apomorphies.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
Combination of the following characters: (1) Rectangular valvae, distally concave along margin (Fig. 27a), (2) Parallel setae-covered lobes projecting from the valva apodeme (Fig. 27b) (considered 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“transtilla”">&quot;transtilla&quot;</normalizedToken>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="St Laurent, RA" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="57 - 92" title="Revisions of the genera Lurama Schaus, 1928 and Ulmara Schaus, 1928 (Lepidoptera, Mimallonoidea, Mimallonidae) with the descriptions of three new Ulmara species and a new genus." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.611.9058" volume="611" year="2016">St Laurent (2016)</bibRefCitation>
